{
  "text": "For a one-dimensional output y, the inversion of A yy is just a division by a scalar. An alternative derivation can be obtained by taking A as an ellipsoid and by computing the value y that results in the smallest Mahalanobis distance of [x T , y] to the origin [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
